Spain Group Wins Bid to Build $9.9 Billion Saudi Train, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-20T00:18:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-20/spain-group-wins-bid-to-build-9-9-billion-saudi-train-ft-says.html
A group of 11 Spanish companies has
won a 7 billion-euro ($9.9 Billion) contract to build the first
high-speed “pilgrim train” to connect the Muslim holy sites of
Mecca and Medina in  Saudi Arabia , the Financial Times reported,
citing people briefed on the matter.  The companies include trainmaker Patentes Talgo SA,
construction company  Obrascon Huarte Lain SA (OHL)  and  Spain ’s state-
owned rail company Renfe Operadora SC, the FT said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 